cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.SY

This paper deals with the use of neural networks in optimization tasks, specifically in surrogate modeling. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also involves the use of machine learning techniques such as genetic programming and neuroevolution, which are commonly associated with cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The focus on modeling and prediction suggests that cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely category. The robotic navigation task mentioned in the abstract suggests that the paper may also fall under cs.RO (Robotics) or cs.SY (Systems and Control).
